Episodes.Title: See No Evil
Episodes.Plot: A wife and a 9-year-old blind daughter of a Navy captain are kidnapped and the captain is a hostage in his own office, communicating with kidnappers, who watch his every step via computer camera.  NCIS team investigates the scheme where large amount of money is involved.
Episodes.GuestStars: David Keith, William Mapother, Ely Pouget, Brian Dietzen, Audrey Wasilewski, Abigail Breslin

Episodes.Title: The Good Wives Club
Episodes.Plot: A mummified remains of a woman are found in the abandoned compound. The team discovers that the woman was missing for several months, was wearing a wedding dress when she died, and might've been a victim of a serial killer. The search for the murderer leads them to Florida, where they start looking for another woman who mysteriously disappeared after going to work. One of the clues they have is the old manual for good wifes.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kate Hodge, Spencer Garrett, Jerry O'Donnell, Matt Carmody, Brian Dietzen, Betsy Brandt, Tara Buck

Episodes.Title: Vanished
Episodes.Plot: Marine helicopter is disovered in the middle of a crop circle in a rural area and the pilots are missing. Soon, NCIS discoveres that only one of the pilots was on the flight, that there is a decade long feud going on in town, and that the missing pilot is out for revenge.
Episodes.GuestStars: Timothy Bottoms, Tom Bower, Robert Rusler, Jeremy Garrett, Jennifer Hall, Rob Boltin, Don Swayze, Todd Kimsey

Episodes.Title: Lt. Jane Doe
Episodes.Plot: A body of a woman in the Navy uniform is found by two sailors.  Ducky links the murder to an unsolved case from 10 years ago, and the team is searching for the serial killer who leaves the note promising to return.
Episodes.Writer: Steven Long Mitchell, Craig W. Van Sickle, Donald P
Episodes.GuestStars: Amy Sloan, Ben Reed, Jack Kehler, David Marciano, Brian Dietzen, Kent Faulcon, Donnie Jeffcoat, Chris Heuisler, Julia Rose

Episodes.Title: The Bone Yard
Episodes.Plot: NCIS discovers that an area in the Marine's bombing range is where mafia has been dumping the bodies for a while. One of the victims is an undercover FBI agent. The team sets out to find a mole.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Rosenfeld, Robert Costanzo, Chris Ellis, Brian Dietzen, Mary Pat Gleason, Joe Tabb, Blue Deckert, Joe Spano

Episodes.Title: Terminal Leave
Episodes.Plot: The team must protect an Iraq veteran due to the threats made by the terrorists. While trying to convince an FBI Agent Lina Reyes to help them, the team is convinced that they have discovered the bomber. However, more secrets are about to be revealed...
Episodes.GuestStars: Elizabeth Peña, Sean O'Bryan, Amanda Fuller, Rebecca Staab, Tim Ryan, Brian Dietzen, Jesse Head, David Henrie, Mary Page Keller

Episodes.Title: Call of Silence
Episodes.Plot: Ernie Yost, an elder Marine veteran confesses to murdering his best friends almost 60 years ago in a war battle and the NCIS's job is to solve all the secrets and save Ernie from prison.
Episodes.GuestStars: Charles Durning, Alicia Coppola, Garette Ratliff Henson

Episodes.Title: Heart Break
Episodes.Plot: A strange case for Gibbs and his team opens when a Navy Commendar dies after successful surgery. While researching through commander's past, the team finds out that he collected a lot of enemies lately and tracks down a ensign making him the prime suspect. Soon Abby realizes that they got the wrong man...
Episodes.GuestStars: Jessica Steen, Stacy Edwards, Nathan Wetherington, Michael Dempsey, Brian Dietzen, Billy Brown, Charles Walker, Derrex Brady, Tyler Kain

Episodes.Title: Forced Entry
Episodes.Plot: Laura Rowen (guest star Megan Ward), a Marine's wife, shoots an intruder in self defense when he is about to rape her. The team takes upon the case and finds out that the wife is leading a double life while her husband is serving overseas. Allegedly, she has been chatting with a stranger on the net and had no idea about his true intentions. The team believes that she might have lured him to her home, not knowing that he is a serial rapist...
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R13 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Megan Ward, Missy Yager, Neil Hopkins, Lindsay Price, Sterling Macer Jr., Brian Dietzen, Josh Daugherty

Episodes.Title: Chained
Episodes.Plot: Tony disappears while doing an undercover operation as an escaped prisoner who is forced to stick to a convinct that owns a key to an expensive ancient Iraqi sculpture. The GPS locator that Abby planted on Tony stops working and the team is forced to find Tony before he gets murdered by the thief.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: R13 Violence and content that may disturb
Episodes.GuestStars: Annie Corley, John Thaddeus, Don S. Davis, Miguel Pérez, Frank Whaley

Episodes.Title: Black Water
Episodes.Plot: A dead body of a 2-year-missing Navy officer appears on the bottom of a lake. The team investigates the case with a help of a private detective. Meanwhile, a famous family offers a lot of money in exchange for the information about the missing body. The team is surprised when a bullet is found in a car. Now the dissapereance becomes a murder...
Episodes.Writer: Juan Carlos Coto, John C. Kelley
Episodes.GuestStars: Mike Starr, Michael Weaver, Robin Riker, Brian Dietzen, Mark D. Espinoza, Lorna Scott, Jimmy Palumbo

Episodes.Title: Doppelgänger
Episodes.Plot: The team takes upon another strange case when a telemarketer reports a possible murder of a petty officer who appeared to be dying over the phone. However, with the help of Virginia officials, the team finds out that officer's call was just a big joke using the computer skills, until he is actually found dead...
Episodes.GuestStars: John Doman, Chad Willett, Rebecca McFarland, Kimberly Oja, Rob Benedict, Will Burke, Willie C. Carpenter, Grant Garrison, Jeremy Guskin, Craig Welzbacher

Episodes.Title: The Meat Puzzle
Episodes.Plot: A "meat puzzle" starts when Ducky identifies the pieces of three bodies that were stuffed inside a barrel few months ago and they turn out to be bodies of a judge, prosecutor and jury foreman that worked with Ducky on a rape case 10 years ago. Gibbs believes that Ducky might be the next victim of the killer, so he orders the team to keep him and his mother safe. Even so, Ducky is kidnapped during the investigation and now the team must find him before it's too late.
Episodes.GuestStars: Pat Healy, Lee Garlington, Holmes Osborne, Brian Dietzen, Morgan Weisser, Jesse D. Goins, Nina Foch

Episodes.Title: Witness
Episodes.Plot: Erin Kendall (guest star Danica McKellar) claims to have seen a murder of a sailor in an apartment across from hers. Gibbs assigns the case to McGee who believes that he can resolve it himself. However, due to the lack of physical evidence, McGee turns to the team to help him...
Episodes.GuestStars: Jack McGee, Danica McKellar, Tina Lifford, Conor Dubin, Brian Dietzen, Colleen Porch, Christopher Stapleton

Episodes.Title: Caught on Tape
Episodes.Plot: The team takes on a case of a dead Marine who recorded his death while falling off a cliff. The prime suspects are his wife and his best friend with whom he had a picnic in the camp. Gibbs finds out they had an affair behind the dead man's back and he tries to persuade each of them to blame each other. Meanwhile, Abby reconstructs the case using her computer skills to handler the Marine's camera...
Episodes.Writer: Christopher Crowe, John C. Kelley, Gil Grant
Episodes.GuestStars: Tim De Zarn, Marieh Delfino, David Lipper, Kevin Sizemore, Brian Dietzen, John Lacy

Episodes.Title: Pop Life
Episodes.Plot: NCIS starts the investigation after petty officer Manda King is found dead in the bartender's bed. The suspect is the owner of the competing club where Manda's sister sings.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mya Harrison, Steven Brand, Scott Alan Smith, Conrad Roberts, Brian Dietzen, Kiko Ellsworth, Daya Vaidya, Shang Forbes

Episodes.Title: An Eye for an Eye
Episodes.Plot: When a sailor officer receives a pair of blue eyeballs, the NCIS team starts investigating the case. Gibbs comes on a trace for a past Navy agent that does illegal work.
Episodes.GuestStars: Anthony Heald, Brian Dietzen, Carlos Lacamara, Madison Mason, Mark Adair-Rios, Cleo King, Daniel Jay Shore, Tania Raymonde

Episodes.Title: Bikini Wax
Episodes.Plot: A petty officer that just returned to his job is found dead in the backstage of the bikini contest. The team finds out that she possibly had a stalker behind her back...
Episodes.GuestStars: Tamara Craig Thomas, Lochlyn Munro, Brian Dietzen, Jon Sklaroff, Lamont Thompson, Larry Cedar, Nathan Anderson, Emma Bates, Teck Holmes

Episodes.Title: Conspiracy Theory
Episodes.Plot: The team investigates a suicide case, believing that the main reason of her death is a nervous breakdown, but Ducky believes that she was actually murdered. FBI Special Agent Fornell helps them in the investigation. The team discovers that the dead woman was involved in a love triangle and that this may have contributed to her death.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brigid Brannagh, Dan Ziskie, Jennifer Dundas, Brian Dietzen, Hilary Angelo, Molly Hagan, Dean McDermott, Kevin Quigley, Jonathan Redford, Joe Spano

Episodes.Title: Red Cell
Episodes.Plot: After a marine is murdered in the school campus the team discovers a possible suspect for his murder, but they are soon leaded back to zero point when they find the suspect murdered. Tim & Abby discover a trace to a ""Red Cell"" in the e-mails and the team believes that maybe the marine was involved in a serious game...
Episodes.GuestStars: Jeff Wincott, Sherman Augustus, Brian Dietzen, Matt DeCaro, Jon Wellner, Judd Trichter, Kaj-Erik Eriksen, Billy Aaron Brown, Chase Ryan Jeffery

Episodes.Title: Hometown Hero
Episodes.Plot: A young Marine is killed in Iraq, but he was investigated by police for a murder on a young girl in his hometown. While going through his personal belongings, they find the body of that girl. The local police believes that the corpsman murdered the girl, but Gibbs believes that he is innocent and he will try to prove it with a help of Faith Coleman (guest star Alicia Coppola).
Episodes.GuestStars: Vincent Angell, Alicia Coppola, Brian Dietzen, Shashawnee Hall, Anne Judson-Yager, Zack Ward, Elizabeth Connors, Matt Bushell, Paul Rae

Episodes.Title: SWAK
Episodes.Plot: When Tony opens a mysterious letter thinking it's for him, a small puff of white powder comes out and it releases a possible deadly virus. Kate calls for help and soon she and Tony are isolated in a bio-hazard isolation room for precausion. McGee and Gibbs work to discover who sent the envelope and how to cure their friends before its too late for them. Meanwhile, Tony's health gets worse...
Episodes.GuestStars: Steven Eckholdt, Mariette Hartley, Tamara Taylor, Brian Dietzen, Olivia Burnette, Kelsey Oldershaw, Rizwan Manji

Episodes.Title: Twilight
Episodes.Plot: A group of serial terrorists seek revenge and send Ari (guest star Rudolf Martin) on an assignment to kill Gibbs. The NCIS team goes on a hunt after him, but when they discover that Ari has a bigger plan, it is already too late... the NCIS team will have to face the death of one of their team members...
Episodes.GuestStars: Rudolf Martin, Brian Dietzen, Benjamin John Parrillo, Shane Conrad, Dennis Cockrum, Alan Dale, Joe Spano
